@startuml Supabase Sync Flow
!theme vibrant
title LilyFit - Cloud Synchronization Flow (Supabase)

actor User
participant "AppProvider" as Provider
participant "SupabaseService" as Supabase
participant "SharedPreferences" as LocalDB
participant "PostgreSQL\n(Supabase)" as CloudDB
participant "Auth System" as Auth
participant "RLS Policies" as RLS

== Initial Authentication ==

User -> Provider: App launches
activate Provider

Provider -> Supabase: getCurrentUser()
activate Supabase

Supabase -> Auth: Check session
activate Auth

alt Session Valid
    Auth --> Supabase: User object with token
    deactivate Auth

    Supabase --> Provider: Authenticated user

else Session Expired
    Auth --> Supabase: null
    deactivate Auth
    Supabase --> Provider: Not authenticated
    Provider --> User: Navigate to login
end

deactivate Supabase

== Dual Storage Strategy ==

Provider -> Provider: Load from local first
Provider -> LocalDB: Get cached data
activate LocalDB

LocalDB --> Provider: - Profile\n- Meal logs\n- Weight entries\n- Settings
deactivate LocalDB

Provider --> User: Display local data (instant)

Provider -> Supabase: Fetch cloud data
activate Supabase

Supabase -> Auth: Verify JWT token
activate Auth
Auth -> RLS: Check row-level security
activate RLS
RLS --> Auth: User authorized
deactivate RLS
Auth --> Supabase: Proceed
deactivate Auth

Supabase -> CloudDB: SELECT * FROM user_profiles\nWHERE id = $user_id
activate CloudDB
CloudDB --> Supabase: Profile data
deactivate CloudDB

Supabase -> CloudDB: SELECT * FROM meal_logs\nWHERE user_id = $user_id\nAND date >= $last_sync
activate CloudDB
CloudDB --> Supabase: Recent meals
deactivate CloudDB

Supabase -> CloudDB: SELECT * FROM weight_logs\nWHERE user_id = $user_id
activate CloudDB
CloudDB --> Supabase: Weight history
deactivate CloudDB

Supabase --> Provider: Cloud data bundle
deactivate Supabase

Provider -> Provider: Merge strategies:\n- Profile: cloud overwrites local\n- Meals: merge by timestamp\n- Weight: keep latest per day

Provider -> LocalDB: Update cache with merged data
activate LocalDB
LocalDB --> Provider: Saved
deactivate LocalDB

Provider -> Provider: notifyListeners()
Provider --> User: Update UI with synced data

deactivate Provider

== Save Profile (Write Flow) ==

User -> Provider: Update profile
activate Provider

Provider -> LocalDB: Save immediately (local-first)
activate LocalDB
LocalDB --> Provider: Saved locally ✓
deactivate LocalDB

Provider --> User: Show success (instant feedback)

Provider -> Supabase: saveUserProfile(profile)
activate Supabase

Supabase -> Auth: Verify authentication
activate Auth
Auth --> Supabase: JWT valid
deactivate Auth

Supabase -> CloudDB: INSERT INTO user_profiles\nON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE\nSET name=$1, age=$2, ...
activate CloudDB

CloudDB -> RLS: Check policy:\nUSER_ID matches authenticated user
activate RLS
RLS --> CloudDB: ✓ Authorized
deactivate RLS

CloudDB -> CloudDB: Execute UPSERT
CloudDB -> CloudDB: Trigger: sync email from auth.users

CloudDB --> Supabase: Success (1 row affected)
deactivate CloudDB

Supabase --> Provider: Profile synced to cloud ✓
deactivate Supabase

note right of Provider
  **Local-First Benefits:**
  1. Instant UI updates
  2. Works offline
  3. No waiting for network
  4. Resilient to failures

  Cloud sync happens in background
end note

== Log Meal (Write Flow) ==

User -> Provider: addMeal(food, mealType, servings)
activate Provider

Provider -> Provider: Create MealLog object
Provider -> LocalDB: Append to meal_logs array
activate LocalDB
LocalDB --> Provider: Saved locally ✓
deactivate LocalDB

Provider -> Provider: Update consumed totals
Provider -> Provider: notifyListeners()
Provider --> User: Meal appears in UI immediately

Provider -> Supabase: logMeal({...mealData})
activate Supabase

Supabase -> Auth: Verify token
activate Auth
Auth --> Supabase: Valid
deactivate Auth

Supabase -> CloudDB: INSERT INTO meal_logs (\n  user_id, meal_type, food_name,\n  calories, protein, carbs, fat,\n  servings, date\n) VALUES ($1, $2, ...)
activate CloudDB

CloudDB -> RLS: Enforce: user_id = auth.uid()
activate RLS
RLS --> CloudDB: ✓ Pass
deactivate RLS

CloudDB -> CloudDB: Insert meal log
CloudDB --> Supabase: Inserted (id: abc123)
deactivate CloudDB

Supabase --> Provider: Meal synced ✓
deactivate Supabase

alt Sync Failed (Network Error)
    Supabase --> Provider: Error (timeout)
    Provider -> Provider: Mark meal as "pending sync"
    Provider -> LocalDB: Add to sync queue
    activate LocalDB
    LocalDB --> Provider: Queued
    deactivate LocalDB

    note right of Provider
      Retry later when online:
      - On app resume
      - Periodic background check
      - Manual sync button
    end note
end

deactivate Provider

== Real-Time Subscription ==

User -> Provider: App in foreground
activate Provider

Provider -> Supabase: subscribeToProfile(onUpdate)
activate Supabase

Supabase -> Supabase: Create WebSocket channel:\n"profile_changes"

Supabase -> CloudDB: LISTEN ON postgres_changes\nFOR user_profiles\nWHERE id = $user_id
activate CloudDB

CloudDB --> Supabase: Subscribed to changes
deactivate CloudDB

Supabase --> Provider: Channel active
deactivate Supabase

... Some time later ...

CloudDB -> Supabase: NOTIFY: Profile updated\n(from another device)
activate CloudDB
activate Supabase

Supabase -> Auth: Verify subscription auth
activate Auth
Auth --> Supabase: Valid
deactivate Auth

Supabase -> Provider: onUpdate(newProfile)

Provider -> Provider: Merge remote changes
Provider -> LocalDB: Update local cache
activate LocalDB
LocalDB --> Provider: Updated
deactivate LocalDB

Provider -> Provider: notifyListeners()
Provider --> User: UI updates seamlessly\n(sync from other device)

deactivate Supabase
deactivate CloudDB

deactivate Provider

== Sync Queue (Offline Support) ==

User -> User: Device goes offline
User -> Provider: Continue using app
activate Provider

Provider -> LocalDB: All writes go to local storage
activate LocalDB
LocalDB --> Provider: Saved (offline mode)
deactivate LocalDB

Provider --> User: App works normally

Provider -> Provider: Queue sync operations:\n- meal_1: pending\n- weight_1: pending\n- profile_update: pending

User -> User: Device back online

Provider -> Provider: Detect connectivity restored

Provider -> Supabase: Process sync queue
activate Supabase

loop For each pending operation
    Provider -> Supabase: Sync operation

    Supabase -> CloudDB: Execute deferred write
    activate CloudDB

    alt Success
        CloudDB --> Supabase: Success
        deactivate CloudDB
        Supabase --> Provider: Synced ✓
        Provider -> LocalDB: Mark as synced
        activate LocalDB
        LocalDB --> Provider: Updated
        deactivate LocalDB

    else Conflict (data changed remotely)
        CloudDB --> Supabase: Conflict detected
        deactivate CloudDB
        Provider -> Provider: Resolve conflict:\n- Last-write-wins\n- Or user prompt
    end
end

Supabase --> Provider: All operations synced
deactivate Supabase

Provider --> User: Show notification:\n"✅ All data synced to cloud"

deactivate Provider

== Row Level Security (RLS) ==

note right of RLS
  **Security Policies:**

  user_profiles:
  - SELECT: WHERE id = auth.uid()
  - INSERT: WHERE id = auth.uid()
  - UPDATE: WHERE id = auth.uid()
  - DELETE: WHERE id = auth.uid()

  meal_logs:
  - SELECT: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
  - INSERT: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
  - UPDATE: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
  - DELETE: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()

  weight_logs:
  - SELECT: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
  - INSERT: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
  - DELETE: WHERE user_id = auth.uid()

  foods:
  - SELECT: PUBLIC (all users)
  - INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE: Admin only

  **Result:**
  Users can ONLY access their own data.
  No way to read other users' information.
end note

== Data Flow Summary ==

note left of Provider
  **Write Flow:**
  1. User action
  2. Save to local (instant)
  3. Update UI (instant)
  4. Sync to cloud (background)
  5. Handle errors gracefully

  **Read Flow:**
  1. Load from local (instant)
  2. Show data immediately
  3. Fetch from cloud (background)
  4. Merge updates
  5. Refresh UI if needed

  **Benefits:**
  - Fast user experience
  - Works offline
  - Automatic sync
  - Conflict resolution
  - Secure (RLS)
end note

== Sync Status Indicator ==

User -> Provider: Check sync status
activate Provider

Provider -> Provider: Calculate:\n- Last sync time\n- Pending operations count\n- Network status

Provider --> User: Show indicator:\n- ✅ Synced (1 min ago)\n- ⏳ Syncing... (2 items)\n- ⚠️ Offline (5 pending)\n- ❌ Sync failed (retry)

User -> Provider: Pull to refresh (manual sync)

Provider -> Supabase: Force sync all data
activate Supabase
Supabase --> Provider: Sync complete
deactivate Supabase

Provider --> User: "✅ Up to date"

deactivate Provider

@enduml

